trans-unit.source: Represents an element in a <xref href="System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElementCollection"></xref> class.
The <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElementCollection> class represents the \<schemeSettings> element under the Uri section within a configuration file.
The <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement> class represents an instance of an element in the <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElementCollection> class.

The <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElementCollection> class and the \<schemeSettings> section in a configuration file looks generic, implying that an application can specify any <xref:System.GenericUriParserOptions?displayProperty=fullName> enumeration value for any scheme.
In fact, only the <xref:System.GenericUriParserOptions?displayProperty=fullName> flag for HTTP and HTTPS schemes are supported.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement"></xref> class.
Gets the value of the GenericUriParserOptions entry from a <xref href="System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement"></xref> instance.

The <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement.GenericUriParserOptions%2A> property returns a <xref:System.GenericUriParserOptions?displayProperty=fullName> enumeration value for the <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement> instance.
Gets the value of the Name entry from a <xref href="System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement"></xref> instance.

The <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement.GenericUriParserOptions%2A> property returns a <xref:System.GenericUriParserOptions?displayProperty=fullName> enumeration value for the <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement> instance.
The <xref:System.Configuration.SchemeSettingElement.GenericUriParserOptions%2A> element is currently restricted to HTPP and HTTPS.
The protocol used by this schema setting.
